<li id="cite_note-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFChomsky1956">Chomsky, Noam (1956). "<a href="http://www.chomsky.info/articles/195609--.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.chomsky.info/articles/195609--.pdf" rel="nofollow">Three models for the description of language</a>". <i>IRE Transactions on Information Theory</i> <b>2</b>: 113–124. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1109%2FTIT.1956.1056813" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1109%2FTIT.1956.1056813" rel="nofollow">10.1109/TIT.1956.1056813</a></span><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.chomsky.info/articles/195609--.pdf" class="external free" title="http://www.chomsky.info/articles/195609--.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://www.chomsky.info/articles/195609--.pdf</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Three+models+for+the+description+of+language&amp;rft.jtitle=IRE+Transactions+on+Information+Theory&amp;rft.aulast=Chomsky&amp;rft.aufirst=Noam&amp;rft.au=Chomsky%2C+Noam&amp;rft.date=1956&amp;rft.volume=2&amp;rft.pages=113%E2%80%93124&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1109%2FTIT.1956.1056813&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.chomsky.info%2Farticles%2F195609--.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Transformational_grammar"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
